{"TopicId":167227,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Horten 229","CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T14:44:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T14:44:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInspired by a thread by someone who was having problems achieving stable flight with their own Horten, I thought I would build one to see if it was possible.\u00A0 This is my effort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Horten.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.88qv.com/KSP/Horten.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/E77fMzl_6k8?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003EPilot Notes\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake off speed is around 60 m/s\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis Horten is sedate rather than spirited, so controls are a bit slow\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAction group key 3 will toggle the airbrakes, though like the other controls, they aren\u0027t overly effective\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t try steering on the ground at higher speeds, as it has a wicked tendency to ground loop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCraft file can be downloaded from Dropbox\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/teohb853huq2zuw/Horten.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/teohb853huq2zuw/Horten.craft?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-05T14:45:50Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2017 02:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Scarecrow\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T21:26:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeed to learn to fly it with custom action groups so you can use spoilers for yaw control\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224surfRightYaw.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022754\u0022 src=\u0022http://ardupilot.org/plane/_images/4surfRightYaw.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T21:58:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509917193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022selfish_meme\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, selfish_meme said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeed to learn to fly it with custom action groups so you can use spoilers for yaw control\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOR rebind some keys (numpad maybe) to action groups\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T22:44:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, it\u0027s a lot easier to cheat and fit a vertical stabiliser inside the fuselage.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eagle92lightning","CreatedById":170551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-07T20:22:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have tried a few flying wings and one fully stock one made by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149419-servo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149419\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149419-servo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Servo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0or \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/139039-northamericanaviation/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022139039\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/139039-northamericanaviation/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NorthAmericanAviation\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(Sorry can\u0027t remember who made the B-2) can fly very nicely except for a slight pitch down but that has nothing to do with the yaw control. Now what is probably causing the side slip is your yaw ability on the yaw axis I am assuming it is running off of Whesely turbo-fans.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-08T07:30:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223213421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510086127\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eagle92lightning\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, eagle92lightning said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have tried a few flying wings and one fully stock one made by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149419-servo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149419\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149419-servo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Servo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0or \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/139039-northamericanaviation/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022139039\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/139039-northamericanaviation/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NorthAmericanAviation\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(Sorry can\u0027t remember who made the B-2) can fly very nicely except for a slight pitch down but that has nothing to do with the yaw control. Now what is probably causing the side slip is your yaw ability on the yaw axis I am assuming it is running off of Whesely turbo-fans.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it is running on Wheesleys but to be honest, it doesn\u0027t suffer that much from sideslip.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eagle92lightning","CreatedById":170551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-08T11:53:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223213781\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510126238\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002265767\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Scarecrow said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it is running on Wheesleys but to be honest, it doesn\u0027t suffer that much from sideslip.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... That\u0027s interesting but remmer the Ho 229 Horton was sitting duck in the sky for P-51s except for the fact that it had jets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"chadgaskerman","CreatedById":155837,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T21:09:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223213862\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510141998\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eagle92lightning\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 08/11/2017 at 11:53 AM, eagle92lightning said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... That\u0027s interesting but remmer the Ho 229 Horton was sitting duck in the sky for P-51s except for the fact that it had jets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou also have to remember it was a heavy fighter designed to carry a 1000kg bomb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eagle92lightning","CreatedById":170551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T21:44:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223216131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510348147\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022chadgaskerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, chadgaskerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou also have to remember it was a heavy fighter designed to carry a 1000kg bomb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}